     <h5 class="pt-3">Instructions</h5>
     <p>Your task is to remember pairs of words, and then your memory for those pairs will be tested.</p>

     <p>First you will be shown each pair of words for 7 seconds. Try to remember the pairs.</p>

     <p>After all word pairs have been shown your memory for each word pair will be tested:
	 <ul> 
	   <li>You will be shown the first word in a pair and asked to enter the second word.</li> 
	   <li>You will be told whether your answer was correct or not, and the correct answer will be displayed.</li> 
	   <li>If you get the answer wrong please try to remember the correct answer.</li> 
	   <li>Each word pair will be tested multiple times.</li>
	 </ul>
     </p>

     <p>You will be given a practice trial to understand the test process. This will use a short list, with only three word pairs. This is only to help you get familiar with the process; the results are not part of the study. You can repeat the practice trial as many times as you like before starting the main part of the study.</p>

     <p>Try to work quickly, but without rushing.</p>

